list.abstract: rent（英[rent]，美[rent]），英语单词。可做名词或动词用。做名词时，指房租、地租、裂缝等；做动词时，指租借、租用、出租等。英语短语有ground rent（地租），例句为The company also allows people to rent some booths to change them as they want to.（该公司还允许人们租用一些摊位，根据自己的意愿进行更换）。 复数为rents；原形为rend；第三人称单数为rents；现在分词为renting；过去式为rented；过去分词为rented。 近义词有letting、hire、lease out等。
《吉屋出租》（Rent）是由克里斯·哥伦布执导，克里斯·哥伦布、Jonathan Larson、斯蒂芬·卓博斯基编剧，安东尼·拉普、亚当·帕斯考、罗莎里奥·道森、杰西·马丁、威尔森·杰梅因·贺雷迪亚等主演的爱情歌舞电影，于2005年11月23日在美国上映。 影片根据百老汇获得托尼奖的音乐剧改编而来，讲述了三对有情人的亲情、友情和爱情的故事。

yingyinNormal.en: How were they paying for the rent on the house?
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们是拿什么付租金的？

yingyinNormal.en: But more important, because of rent control, it was a frigging steal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 更重要的是租金管制简直就是明抢啊。

yingyinNormal.en: I have a three-bedroom on 5th. It's half this rent. I like this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 五楼还有一套三室的公寓，租金只要这里的一半。我喜欢这套。

yingyinNormal.en: He can sleep in the apartment upstairs? No. We need the rent to pay the mortgage.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他可以住楼上的公寓？不。我们需要租金来还贷款。

yingyinNormal.en: Will you rent me your gear for the day?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的枪能租给我用一天吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Your business is booming, and now I want rent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的生意火了，我要收店租。

yingyinNormal.en: No rent, han. That wasn't the deal you made us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不能收租，Han 你当初可不是这么说的。

yingyinNormal.en: That's it, your business is booming, I want rent. 200.
yingyinNormal.zh: 够了，你的生意好了，我要房租 200刀。

yingyinNormal.en: Are these for rent. I thought people were just bragging.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些是要租的吗？我以为他们是在炫耀自己的房子有多棒。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you rent phones?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你这儿有租手机业务吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Rent-free? Now, refresh my memory. When exactly did I say rent-free?
yingyinNormal.zh: 免费? 容我想想，我啥时候说"免费"了?

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. Okay, what else? Rent. Okay, two, three years of rent, utilities, food.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，还有呢？房租两、三年的房租、杂费、伙食费…

yingyinNormal.en: You don't know how much your rent is? My father pays for it! Do you know how much your rent is?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你连自己的房租都不知道吗？我爸帮我付房租啦，你知道你的房租多少钱吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Do you remember that rent is due next week? Probably not.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还记得下星期就要付房租吗? 大概不记得了吧?

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, I just, I need it for some rent and some other bills.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别这样，我只是我需要付房租跟一些帐单。

yingyinNormal.en: Scorpio was a very good book. Still pays the rent. Have a seat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 《天蝎》这书很不错。够糊口而已。请坐。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you tell Dan? What? You did. You told your low-rent boyfriend.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你给丹说了？什么？你告诉他了，你告诉了你的穷酸男朋友。

yingyinNormal.en: He's trying to save up to build inventory, and rent is killing him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他想省下钱来多做一些产品，但房租快逼死他了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well. Why don't we go down to the elephant lot and rent an elephant?
yingyinNormal.zh: 要不我们去大象堆里借一头大象？

yingyinNormal.en: It tells me that I am living rent free right here. You ready to bowl?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这说明你无时无刻都在想着我，准备好比赛了么？

examination_example.sentence: I can't afford to pay my monthly mortgage payments on my own, so I have to <highlight>rent</highlight> rooms out to people to make that happen.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我自己付不起每月的抵押贷款，所以我不得不把房间租给别人来达成这一目标。

word_usage.usage:
rent sth. from sb. 意为“从……借某物”，rent sth. to sb. 意为“将某物租给……”，如：
Tom rented this house from Mr Little, and rented two rooms to Mrs Addams. 
汤姆向利特尔先生租了这所房子，又把两个房间租给亚当斯太太。

examination_example.sentence: Sarina Harpet, a 19-year-old student at Virginia Tech, was faced with a tough dilemma when she first started college in 2015— pay <highlight>rent</highlight> or pay to turn in her chemistry homework.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 弗吉尼亚理工大学19岁的学生萨琳娜·哈珀(Sarina Harpet)在2015年刚上大学的时候，面临着一个艰难的两难选择：交房租还是花钱交化学作业。

examination_example.sentence: She <highlight>rented</highlight> her economics and statistics textbooks for about $ 20 each. But her access codes for homework, which can't be <highlight>rented</highlight> or bought second-hand, were her most expensive purchases: $ 120 and $ 85.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她租了经济学和统计学的课本，每本约20美元。但她的作业的访问码，不能租也不能买二手，是她买的最贵的东西：120美元和85美元。

examination_example.sentence: The code to access the program cost $ 120— a big sum for Harper, who had already put down $ 450 for textbooks, and had <highlight>rent</highlight> day approaching.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 访问该程序的代码需要花费120美元，这对哈珀来说是一大笔钱，她已经花了450美元买了教科书，而且房租日也快到了。

examination_example.sentence: This year she said she spent $ 900 on access codes to books and programs. That's two months of <highlight>rent</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年，她说她花了900美元购买书籍和程序的访问代码。这相当于两个月的租金。
